        {
            "id": "tradingview:6dff3af771e19:0",
            "title": "RESOURCES CONNECTION, INC. FY 2026: Revenue $452.01M, EPS ($1.21) — 10-K Summary",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-Xl9a4Ubk body-nzzZVyQ3 content-nzzZVyQ3\"><div class=\"symbolsContainer-uFduEtAF logosContainer-diQOvrPB\" data-no-swipe=\"true\"></div><div><span><p class=\"\"><span>RESOURCES CONNECTION, INC. reported fiscal 2026 results with revenue of $452.01M, down from $551.33M a year earlier, and a net loss of ($40.6M) compared with a ($191.78M) loss in the prior year; diluted loss per share improved to ($1.21) from ($5.8).</span></p><p class=\"\"><strong class=\"root-Tkn6WL2y\"><span>Financial Highlights</span></strong></p><div class=\"tableContainer-VG8_37yK\"><table class=\"table-VG8_37yK\" data-no-swipe=\"true\"><tbody><tr><td><span>Metric</span></td><td><span>Current year</span></td><td><span>Prior year</span></td><td><span>YoY change</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Revenue¹</span></td><td><span>$452.01M</span></td><td><span>$551.33M</span></td><td><span>(18%)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Net income²</span></td><td><span>($40.6M)</span></td><td><span>($191.78M)</span></td><td><span>78.8%</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Diluted EPS³</span></td><td><span>($1.21)</span></td><td><span>($5.8)</span></td><td><span>79.1%</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p class=\"\"><em><span>¹ Reported as “Revenue”. ² Reported as “Net income (loss)”. ³ Reported as “Net income (loss) per common share”.</span></em></p><p class=\"\"><strong class=\"root-Tkn6WL2y\"><span>Business Highlights</span></strong></p><ul class=\"list-bmN0_SHH list--padded-bmN0_SHH\"><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Revenue fell about 18% year over year, driven by a 17.5% decline in billable hours and weaker demand for traditional accounting skills.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Demand mix shifted from on‑demand operational roles toward AI, automation and higher‑value consulting; U.S. bill rates rose while the overall mix lowered the company’s average rate.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Management integrated Reference Point into a single consulting unit and expanded M&amp;A, data analytics and AI capabilities, while refreshing consultant skillsets.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Launched a 2026 Transformation Initiative that included two rounds of workforce reductions, office footprint optimizations and $8.4M of restructuring to reduce SG&amp;A and streamline operations.</span></li><li class=\"listItem-bmN0_SHH\"><span>Sold Sitrick in May 2026 to simplify the portfolio, realizing $1.9M of proceeds while retaining limited lease-related obligations.</span></li></ul><p class=\"\"><span>Original SEC Filing: </span><a class=\"link-zw5jRdec icon-zw5jRdec\" href=\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1084765/000108476526000051/rgp-20260530.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RESOURCES CONNECTION, INC. [ RGP ] - 10-K - Jul. 24, 2026</a></p><section class=\"variant-secondary-Gmpzg_mv disclaimer-PlF2Sa64\"><b class=\"heading-wrapper-Gmpzg_mv\"><span class=\"heading-Gmpzg_mv\">Disclaimer</span></b><div class=\"content-Gmpzg_mv link-with-underline-Gmpzg_mv\"><span>This is an AI-powered summary. It may contain inaccuracies. Consider verifying important information with the source. Please note this summary is solely based on documents filed with the SEC.</span></div></section></span></div></div>",
            "link": "https://www.tradingview.com/news/tradingview:6dff3af771e19:0-resources-connection-inc-fy-2026-revenue-452-01m-eps-1-21-10-k-summary/",
            "pub_date": "2026-07-25 03:05:05",
            "source": "TradingView",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
